description: Returns a list of FindingsReportSummary objects that contain analysis results for all profiling groups in your AWS account.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: The nextToken value returned from a previous paginated GetFindingsReportAccountSummary request where maxResults was used and the results exceeded the value of that parameter. Pagination continues from the end of the previous results that returned the nextToken value.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The nextToken value to include in a future GetFindingsReportAccountSummary request. When the results of a GetFindingsReportAccountSummary request exceed maxResults, this value can be used to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.

nested_items.name: reportSummaries
nested_items.description: The return list of FindingsReportSummary objects taht contain summaries of analysis results for all profiling groups in your AWS account.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The universally unique identifier (UUID) of the recommendation report.

nested_items.name: profileEndTime
nested_items.description: The end time of the period during which the metric is flagged as anomalous. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

nested_items.name: profileStartTime
nested_items.description: The start time of the profile the analysis data is about. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

nested_items.name: profilingGroupName
nested_items.description: The name of the profiling group that is associated with the analysis data.

nested_items.name: totalNumberOfFindings
nested_items.description: The total number of different recommendations that were found by the analysis.
